            "answer_text": "A mix of both depending on when you\u2019re talking about plus other dating conventions. Particularly after Justinian, official documents used a cycle of indictions, a period of fifteen years which was used to schedule certain kinds of important tax assessments and the like. And from the tenth century on, the Byzantines officially used an anno mundi calendar. The AM calendar dated things from the supposed beginning of the world as calculated from the Bible. For this, they calculated a date around 5507 BC. ",
